	"metadata": {
		"title": "libvpx: Integer overflow in vpx_img_alloc() (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-5197",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-5197",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: There exists interger overflows in libvpx in versions prior to 1.14.1. Calling vpx_img_alloc() with a large value of the d_w, d_h, or align parameter may result in integer overflows in the calculations of buffer sizes and offsets and some fields of the returned vpx_image_t struct may be invalid. Calling vpx_img_wrap() with a large value of the d_w, d_h, or stride_align parameter may result in integer overflows in the calculations of buffer sizes and offsets and some fields of the returned vpx_image_t struct may be invalid. We recommend upgrading to version 1.14.1 or beyond",
